SIMPLE: codger
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Codger
<hw>Codg"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Cadger</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A miser or mean
person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A singular or odd person, especially an old man; --
a familiar, humorous, or depreciatory appellation.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A few of us old <qex>codgers</qex> met at the fireside.</q>
<rj><qau>Emerson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Codical</ent>⟦br⟧
